title: Bad
notes:
Includes printed inner-sleeve containing lyrics and credits.

Issued with a variety of hype stickers.
• Some initial copies with a [url=https://www.discogs.com/Michael-Jackson-Bad/release/247822#images/28627673]red sticker[/url] on cover: "Includes the smash hits 'I Just Can't Stop Loving You' 'Bad' 450290 1";
• Some copies with a [url=https://www.discogs.com/Michael-Jackson-Bad/release/247822#images/42970738]black and white sticker[/url] announcing the European tour;
• Some copies with a [url=https://www.discogs.com/Michael-Jackson-Bad/release/247822#images/42972076]Pepsi sticker[/url], main sponsor of the concert tour;
• Some copies with a [url=https://www.discogs.com/Michael-Jackson-Bad/release/247822#images/50938746]Club-Edition sticker[/url] over the barcode
• Some later copies with an [url=https://www.discogs.com/Michael-Jackson-Bad/release/247822#images/50924640]English[/url] or [url=https://www.discogs.com/Michael-Jackson-Bad/release/247822#images/50933079]German sticker[/url] referencing the 1988 movie Moonwalker

Track A3 (Speed Demon):
- Race car intro-Dimensional Recording by Spherical Sound, Inc.

Track B5 (Smooth Criminal):
- Michael Jackson's heartbeat recording by Dr. Eric Chevlen digitally processed in the Synclavier
- Holophonics by Hugo Zuccarelli
- Creaking and heavy breathing by Frank Dileo

Produced for Quincy Jones Productions.
Co-produced for MJJ Productions.
Recorded and mixed using the "Acusonic Recording Process D".
Special thanks to Diana "Lady Di" Douglas

℗ 1987 MJJ Productions Inc.
© 1987 MJJ Productions Inc. 

Made In Holland/Printed in Holland.

Catalog no. 'EPC 450290 1' appears on back cover, labels and spine.
Catalog no. 'OE 40600' appears on labels in parentheses.

[Runout description]:
Etched part of each runout: 'PA(B)L-40600-HOL-(n) (x)'.
Second part of each runout (starts with 01-) is stamped.

identifiers.description: On back- and innersleeve, artwork code, CBS computer#
